#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.201"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.201:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: kimbilavaggo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.201:0.2"
msgid "21. Kimilavagga"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: kimbilasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an5.201:0.3"
msgid "201. Kimilasutta"
msgstr ""

# See BB for the reading nicula=Barringtonia acutangula, https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barringtonia_acutangula
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: kimilāyaṃ → kimbilāyaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.201:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā kimilāyaṃ viharati veḷuvane."
msgstr ""

#. VAR: kimilo → kimbilo (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an5.201:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā kimilo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā kimilo "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""

# This is one sutta where the choice of definite or indefinite article affects the interpretation. See BB’s note. I have used “the”, opting for the less cosmic interpretation. This, it seems to me, avoids the problem of assuming that the text occurs at a time when the comsic Buddha-cycle was well-known.
msgctxt "an5.201:1.3"
msgid ""
"“ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo na "
"ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.201:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Idha, kimila, tathāgate parinibbute bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo "
"satthari agāravā viharanti appatissā, dhamme agāravā viharanti appatissā, "
"saṃghe agāravā viharanti appatissā, sikkhāya agāravā viharanti appatissā, "
"aññamaññaṃ agāravā viharanti appatissā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.201:1.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, kimila, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo na "
"ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.201:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo "
"ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.201:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Idha, kimila, tathāgate parinibbute bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upāsakā upāsikāyo "
"satthari sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, dhamme sagāravā viharanti "
"sappatissā, saṅghe sagāravā viharanti sappatissā, sikkhāya sagāravā "
"viharanti sappatissā, aññamaññaṃ sagāravā viharanti sappatissā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.201:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho, kimila, hetu ayaṃ paccayo, yena tathāgate parinibbute saddhammo "
"ciraṭṭhitiko hotī”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.201:2.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
